      <!-- Section 6: Mental Health Benefits -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Mental Health & Wellbeing Through Competitive Word Games</h2>

      <p>The benefits of Scrabble extend far beyond the board. Regular engagement with mentally stimulating activities like competitive word games contributes to overall psychological wellbeing — reducing stress, building social bonds, and providing a sense of achievement and progressive mastery.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">😌 Stress Reduction</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Focused gameplay creates a flow state — that absorbed, present-moment concentration where daily worries recede. Regular flow-state activities measurably reduce cortisol levels and anxiety symptoms.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🤝 Social Connection</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Club and tournament play builds genuine friendships around shared intellectual pursuit. For older adults especially, regular Scrabble clubs provide vital social interaction that combats isolation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📈 Progressive Mastery</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">The ELO-style rating system in competitive Scrabble provides measurable growth. Watching your rating climb delivers the same satisfaction as fitness milestones — concrete proof that cognitive training is working.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧘 Mindfulness in Practice</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Each turn requires you to be fully present — evaluating the board, weighing options, managing time. This sustained present-moment awareness mirrors meditation practices and improves attention regulation throughout daily life.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-green-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">✅ The Compounding Effect</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Each hour invested in Scrabble training delivers <span class="text-white font-medium">triple returns</span>: improved game performance, measurable cognitive enhancement, and genuine mental health benefits. Unlike pure brain training apps that feel like work, Scrabble is intrinsically motivating — you <em>want</em> to keep playing because it is fun, social, and competitive. That makes it sustainable in a way that isolated cognitive exercises never are.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 7: Practical Tips -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Practical Tips for Accelerating Your Progress</h2>

      <p>These are the tactics that tournament players use to learn faster, retain more, and convert knowledge into points. Each tip integrates the tools available at ScrabbleWordsFinder.com with proven learning science.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Spaced Repetition:</span> Review word lists at increasing intervals (1 day, 3 days, 7 days, 14 days). Each time you recall a word correctly, extend the interval. Use the daily anagram and Word of the Day features as natural spaced repetition anchors.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Active Recall Over Passive Reading:</span> Never just read word lists. Always test yourself first (can you unscramble AEINRST?), then check with the Scrabble word finder. Active recall strengthens memory 3x faster than passive review.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Interleaved Practice:</span> Mix word study with board strategy with endgame drills within a single session. Your brain forms stronger connections when skills are practised in varied contexts rather than blocked repetition.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Track Your Misses:</span> Keep a "missed words" notebook. Every time the instant Scrabble solver shows you a word you did not spot, write it down. Review these weekly — they represent your personal knowledge gaps and the fastest path to improvement.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Play Up:</span> Always seek opponents rated 100-200 points above your level. Losing against stronger players teaches more than winning against weaker ones. Study their plays post-game with the Scrabble solver tool to understand their word choices.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

